<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>cover ground • cover the field</xh5><p> <i>cover ground—</i>1. <i>(also: cover the ground)</i> deal with an assignment, etc. (especially efficiently or rapidly): If you want to <u>cover ground</u> fast, pool your resources. 2. <i>(of a book, etc.)</i> treat a subject: The book could have been greater in scope had the author shown the ambition to <u>cover ground</u> rarely covered in military history.</p><p> <i>cover the field</i>—(also: cover the territory) be comprehensive: The strength of Lister’s book is that it really <u>covers the field</u>, from methodology to practical examples.</p> </entry>
